Colour pattern . Overall dull olive-green or brown with some whitish areas on carapace; chelipeds greenishbrown or brown; walking legs reddish with white articulations; uropod greenish-olive proximally, bluish-grey distally; eggs olive-green ( Figs. 3 , 4 ; see also
Pasternak 1988
;
Marin 2013
).

Distribution . Northwestern Pacific: northern Sea of Japan . Presently known only from a few localities in the Russian Far East (Primorskiy Krai), e.g., Vladivostok area, Peter the Great Bay (= Zaliv Petra Velikogo), Troitza Bay (= Bukhta Troitzy), as well as from Hakodate Bay in southern Hokkaido, Japan (
Fig. 7
).
